<p>V. Kyd's <i>Spanish Tragedy.</i> [Eliot's note]
        Subtitled "Hieronymo's Mad Againe," Kyd's play
        (1594) is an early example of the Elizabethan tragedy of
        revenge. Hieronymo, driven mad by the murder of his son,
        has his revenge when he is asked to write a court
        entertainment. He replies, "Why then Ile fit
        you!" (i.e. accomodate you), and assigns the parts
        of the entertainment so that, in the course of the
        action, his son's murderers are killed. (NA)</p>
